
Activity 3.1


This diagram is an Entity Relationship (ER) Diagram representing a simple Student–Course Management System.
Main Entities
There are 2 tables
1>Student
2>Course

College is relationship between 2 tables ie: student and Course
It shows that:
Students are connected to courses through the college.
A student can enroll in courses offered by the college.


A student belongs to a course.
One course can have many students.
Relationship type: 1 : N


The purpose of this ER diagram is to:
organize student and course information
show how students relate to courses
help design a database for a college management system



Activity 3.2
This diagram shows an Entity Relationship (ER) Diagram for a College Management System. It represents the main entities, their attributes, and the relationships between them.This ER diagram is used to:

-design a college database system
-manage student, course, college, and lecturer data
-show relationships between entities


1> Student

Represents students enrolled in the college.

Attributes:Stud_ID (PK) – Unique student ID
Stud_name – Student name
Stud_email – Student email
Relationship:
A student belongs to a course.


2> Course
Represents academic courses offered by the college.

Attributes:
Crse_id (PK) – Unique course ID
Crse_name – Course name
Relationships:
Students belong to a course
Courses are offered by the college



 3>College
Represents the college institution.

Attributes:
College_ID (PK) – Unique college ID
College_name – Name of the college
College_location – College location
Relationships:
The college offers courses
The college has lecturers


4>Lecturer
Represents lecturers/teachers in the college.

Attributes:
Lec_id – Lecturer ID
Lec_name – Lecturer name
Lec_contact – Lecturer contact number
Lec_email – Lecturer email
Lec_address – Lecturer address
Relationship:
Lecturers teach in the college.